// frequency for letters
// good for small ranges
int freq [26] = {};// init every element to zero u can use vector instead
freq[s[i]-'a']++;

// better for memory optimization
(cant allocate 1e9 array elements)
(so map is better bec it dynmaically allocate only keys you add, array we would allocate 1e9 places and not use some of them)
// log n for insertion in red black tree map
// n for insert in hash map of hashing conflicts occur otherwise o(1)
mp[s[i]-'a']++;

